# Frontend — Next.js (streawman-ui)

## What this app covers

A single Next.js app with two distinct areas:
- **Watch area** — public or permission-gated pages to browse and stream videos/photos
- **Upload area** — restricted section for uploading content (requires elevated permissions)

## Philosophy

- Server Components by default, Client Components only when interactivity requires it
- SSR is a first-class concern — this is explicitly for portfolio demonstration of SSR knowledge
- No client-side data fetching where server fetching is possible

## Directory Structure (inside `apps/streawman-ui/`)

```
src/
├── app/                      ← Next.js App Router pages
│   ├── (watch)/              ← public/viewer-facing routes
│   │   ├── page.tsx          ← home / content listing
│   │   └── [id]/             ← individual video/photo stream page
│   └── (upload)/             ← permission-gated upload routes
│       └── upload/
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                   ← primitive UI components
│   └── features/
│       ├── player/           ← video player and quality switching
│       └── uploader/         ← file upload flow
├── lib/
│   ├── auth.ts               ← [FILL: auth helpers]
│   ├── uploader-api.ts       ← typed wrappers for uploader-api calls
│   └── watcher-api.ts        ← typed wrappers for watcher-api calls
├── hooks/                    ← custom React hooks
└── types/                    ← shared TypeScript types
```

## Rules

- All pages in `app/` are Server Components unless they have `'use client'` at the top
- `'use client'` must have a comment explaining why it can't be a Server Component
- Forms use [FILL: Server Actions or client-side fetch?]
- Styling: **Tailwind CSS** — see ADR 016
- No inline styles except for truly dynamic values (e.g. a width calculated at runtime)
- No arbitrary Tailwind values (`w-[347px]`) unless there is no token that fits — use design tokens first

## Video Player

- Library: **hls.js** — matches the HLS streaming protocol decision (ADR 006)
- Player component lives in `components/features/player/`
- Player requests `master.m3u8` from `watcher-api`; `hls.js` handles quality switching automatically
- Manual quality override UI (resolution selector) is a stretch goal — keep in player component if added
- Player is always a Client Component (`'use client'`) — requires browser MediaSource API
